{
  "stem": "26731.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, so-called children from mixed marriages and partners, mixed marriages were released.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Actually, there were two types of mixed marriages.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One was the so-called mixed marriage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It had one partner Jewish, the other partner not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Those were the regular mixed marriages.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they had the so-called privileged mixed marriages.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They had two wed partners, one not a Jew, one a Jew, but the children were raised as non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They didn't have to wear the star, neither had the Jewish partner to wear the star.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The regular marriages were either without children or children that they raised Jewish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In that case, the children had to wear the star and the Jewish partner had to wear the star.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And those children who were raised Jewish were called Geltungsjuden, meaning they were considered Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They had to wear the star and actually had to do the forced labor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That is a main difference.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was a so-called Geltungsjuden, had to wear the star.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, my mother did not.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father had to, but not my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Had I not been raised Jewish, none of us would have to wear the star.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In my case, it was known.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father had been active in the Jewish congregation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How could we have said that was not the case.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Yes, it was tried.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I know for a fact that some people tried to get out of it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In fact, even at some times, women claimed that their husband wasn't actually the father of the child, that the father was some Aryan.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was tried, too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was tried too-- a case actually of a school-- school friend-- went to the same class.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we did the forced labor together, and he actually one day disappeared.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
